Fitting a straight line to data This notebook is a ~1 hour tutorial on fitting models to data, starting with a linear model and progressing to a linear model with an extra nonlinear parameter (an unknown extra variance to account for unknown error bars or intrinsic scatter).
This notebook is heavily inspired by Hogg et al. 2010, @jakevdp&rsquo;s notes, and parts of the emcee documentation.
